---
import AppPageLayout from '../../../layouts/AppPageLayout.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '../../../site.config';
---

<AppPageLayout
  appName="Imposter"
  pageTitle="Support"
  description="Support and contact information for the Imposter iOS game."
>
  <p>
    Imposter is a pass-and-play party game for iPhone and iPad. Gather a group, pick a number of
    imposters, and try to figure out who doesn't know the secret word.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Need help, have a question, or want to suggest a feature? Email
    <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.email}`}>{siteConfig.email}</a>
    and I'll do my best to get back to you.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Play</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Enter the names of everyone playing (3 or more works best).</li>
    <li>Choose how many imposters there should be.</li>
    <li>Pass the device around. Each player taps their name and long-presses to reveal whether they
      are an imposter and, if not, the secret word. Release to hide it again.</li>
    <li>Once everyone has seen their role, the app picks a random player to start. Discuss, ask
      questions, and try to spot the imposters.</li>
    <li>When you're ready, reveal the imposters and start a new round.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Common Questions</h2>

  <h3>Does Imposter work without an internet connection?</h3>
  <p>Yes. The app is fully offline and does not require a network connection.</p>

  <h3>Are my player names or game data saved?</h3>
  <p>
    No. Names and settings stay in memory only during the current session and are discarded when
    you close the app or start a new game.
  </p>

  <h3>Which devices are supported?</h3>
  <p>Imposter runs on iPhone and iPad with iOS 17 or later.</p>

  <h3>How do I report a bug?</h3>
  <p>
    Send an email to <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.email}`}>{siteConfig.email}</a> with a short
    description of what happened, the device you're using, and the iOS version if you know it.
  </p>
</AppPageLayout>
